## TL;DR: Elongated Cushion Cut Lab Grown Diamond — What to Know First

**An elongated cushion cut lab grown diamond is the best combination of face-up size efficiency, sparkle character, and price-to-quality ratio available in {{year}} — and at 3ct and above, lab is not just the smart choice, it is effectively the only realistic choice, because natural 3ct elongated cushions start at $32,692 while IGI lab equivalents start at $6,215.** Filter your search to L/W ratio 1.15–1.25 (The Ratio Sweet Spot) before anything else — most cushion diamond searches return square stones by default. **→ Best first pick:** [IGI 1.50ct E-VVS2 Cushion Modified Lab-Grown at $1,422](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/28961887?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) — specific stone, real price, elongated cushion modified brilliant sub-type.

**Priority:** IGI over GIA for lab grown stones (same stone quality, 40–60% lower certification cost that passes to buyer price). Filter L/W ratio to 1.15–1.25 — never shop lab cushions by carat alone. At 3ct+, The Lab Sovereign applies: natural supply at any reasonable quality evaporates and lab stones carry D-VVS1 grades at prices that natural 1ct stones cannot reach. The elongated cushion modified brilliant sub-type is the correct pick at every carat tier for the most even sparkle distribution across the longer axis.

