## Elongated Cushion Modified Brilliant Lab Grown

**The elongated cushion modified brilliant is the correct sub-type selection for lab grown elongated cushion diamonds at every carat tier — and understanding why requires understanding what "modified brilliant" means for the elongated cushion specifically.** The cushion modified brilliant sub-type has an additional row of facets on the pavilion compared to the cushion brilliant sub-type, producing a facet pattern that distributes sparkle in smaller, more numerous flash events across the entire face-up area rather than concentrating sparkle in fewer, larger flashes. For elongated cushions, this distributed sparkle pattern is critical: it ensures that both the long ends and the narrow sides of the elongated outline contribute equally to the stone's light return, preventing the "dead zone" appearance at the ends of the elongated axis that can appear in cushion brilliant sub-types at elongated ratios.

At 1.5ct and above, the difference between cushion modified brilliant and cushion brilliant sub-types in elongated ratios is visible at normal examination distance. The modified brilliant produces the "crushed ice" sparkle — a continuous shimmering luminosity that shifts across the entire face-up area as the ring moves — while the cushion brilliant produces larger, more distinct sparkle blocks that leave portions of the face-up area visually dark between flash events. Most buyers who describe an elongated cushion as "glowing" or "luminous" are describing the modified brilliant's crushed ice pattern.

Blue Nile's lab cushion inventory is predominantly cushion modified brilliant sub-type, which means most buyers will naturally end up with the correct sub-type if they search standard cushion filters. When a listing description says "Cushion Modified Lab-Grown Diamond" — as in every specific stone linked in this guide — that confirms the modified brilliant sub-type. Listings that say simply "Cushion Lab-Grown Diamond" without "Modified" may be cushion brilliant sub-type; verify before purchasing by checking the "Cut Style" field in the stone's detail page.

## Best Elongated Cushion Lab Grown Engagement Ring

The elongated cushion cut lab grown engagement ring is where the stone's price advantage becomes most visible in ring-building terms. At a $4,000 total ring budget, a buyer pairing an IGI 2ct D-VVS1 lab cushion at $2,606 with a $1,180 platinum solitaire has money remaining for resizing allowance and still built a ring that a natural diamond buyer cannot reach below $10,000. That budget asymmetry — and the ring-level visibility of what lab pricing enables — is why the elongated cushion lab grown engagement ring has become one of the fastest-growing search categories in the diamond ring market.

Pairing an elongated cushion cut lab grown diamond with the right setting determines whether the stone's L/W ratio advantage is fully expressed or partially concealed. Solitaire settings with four prongs are the standard choice for elongated cushions because the open prong architecture exposes the maximum face-up area — the stone's elongation is visible without obstruction. The [Petite Solitaire 14K White Gold at $1,000](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/petite-solitaire-engagement-ring-item-194386?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) (1,020 reviews) is the most popular entry setting for elongated cushion lab grown diamonds; its narrow, tapered band maximizes stone visual width contrast by providing the thinnest possible band against the elongated face-up.

Settings must be ordered in the correct head size for the specific elongated cushion's L/W ratio — a head calibrated for a 1.00–1.05 square cushion will misalign prongs on a 1.20 elongated stone, either crowding the table or failing to cover corners correctly. When ordering any setting for an elongated cushion lab grown diamond, specify the stone's exact L/W ratio and confirm the setting head accommodates it; at Blue Nile this is a standard customization and the jeweler selects the correct elongated head when stone dimensions are provided. For the full lab grown cushion category guide covering sub-types, certification, and price data across both elongated and square ratios, see [Lab Grown Cushion Cut Diamond](/lab-grown-cushion-cut-diamond).

