## Expert Summary

Metal choice for elongated cushion lab grown engagement rings follows straightforward rules. White gold or platinum is preferred when the stone is D–F colorless — the cool metal maximizes contrast and prevents warmth perception across the elongated face-up area; yellow gold is correct for G–H color, where it neutralizes the slight body color that elongated cushions display more visibly than compact rounds. Rose gold works with either color range and pairs naturally with the elongated cushion's soft corner geometry.

The elongated cushion cut lab grown diamond is the most compelling value proposition in diamond retail in {{year}}: it delivers the cushion shape's soft, distinctive optical character in an elongated format that maximizes face-up size, adds the optical finger-lengthening effect, and does so at lab grown prices that make D-VVS1 quality accessible at 2ct for $2,606 and D-VVS1 quality accessible at 3ct for $5,962. These are not compromise stones — they are genuinely excellent diamonds by every measurable criterion, certified by IGI on the same grading scale as natural stones, with zero visual difference detectable under normal conditions. For a complete guide to the elongated cushion cut shape across both lab and natural origins — including L/W ratio mechanics, face-up size charts, and cutting sub-types — see [Elongated Cushion Cut Diamond](/elongated-cushion-cut-diamond).

The buying sequence for this category that avoids the most common mistakes: filter L/W ratio to 1.15–1.25 before doing anything else; choose IGI certification over GIA for lab stones (40–140% lower cost, no quality difference in the stone); buy cushion modified brilliant sub-type (confirms "Modified" in the listing name); and treat 3ct as The Lab Sovereign tier — at 3ct, the natural elongated cushion market has effectively priced itself out of reach and lab stones are the rational choice for nearly all buyers. The only buyer for whom natural makes unambiguous sense at 3ct is one who will hold the ring as an heirloom asset and values GIA-certified natural provenance above all other criteria.

The one legitimate caveat for lab grown elongated cushion purchases: resale value is minimal. Lab diamond resale at 5–20% of purchase price is not a defect specific to elongated cushions — it applies to all lab grown diamonds — but buyers who might sell the ring in the future should factor it into their decision. For buyers who intend to wear and keep the ring, this caveat is irrelevant.

> "My recommendation for elongated cushion buyers is consistent: go lab grown unless you have a specific heirloom or provenance reason to go natural. The quality you access with lab is genuinely unreachable with natural at these prices. D-VVS1 in a 3ct elongated cushion for $6,000 — that specification would have cost $80,000 in natural five years ago and still does today. The lab market has made quality that was previously reserved for royalty accessible to anyone with a serious engagement ring budget."
> — Farzana, Diamond Consultant

## Final Verdict: Which Elongated Cushion Cut Lab Grown Diamond Should You Buy?

**Best for entry budget (under $3,000 total ring):** [IGI 1.50ct E-VVS2 Cushion Modified Lab at $1,422](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/28961887?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) + [Petite Solitaire 14K White Gold at $1,000](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/petite-solitaire-engagement-ring-item-194386?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) = **$2,422 total**. A 1.5ct E-VVS2 elongated cushion in white gold delivers the elongated cushion look at entry price; at L/W 1.20 it measures 7.7mm × 6.4mm — noticeably larger than any 1ct stone and clearly elongated on the finger.

**Best for maximum quality at mid-budget:** [IGI 2.00ct D-VVS1 Cushion Modified Lab at $2,606](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/28884982?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) + [Classic Four Prong Platinum at $1,180](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/classic-four-prong-solitaire-engagement-ring-item-194156?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) = **$3,786 total**. D color and VVS1 clarity in a 2ct elongated cushion for under $4,000 total ring — this is the category's strongest value build and the most popular combination for buyers who want both impressive size and the best possible measurable quality.

**Best for statement presence (3ct Lab Sovereign tier):** [IGI 3.00ct D-VVS1 Cushion Modified Lab at $6,215](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/25630512?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) + [Riviera Pavé 14K White Gold at $1,515](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/riviera-pave-engagement-ring-item-195326?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) = **$7,730 total**. A 3ct elongated cushion at L/W 1.20 measures approximately 9.5mm × 7.9mm — a genuinely commanding ring that produces maximum elongated cushion presence at The Lab Sovereign price point. D-VVS1 in a pavé band for under $8,000.

**Best for heirloom buyers who want natural:** [GIA 1ct G-VS1 Natural Cushion from $1,891](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-search?shape=cushion&a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) + [Classic Four Prong Solitaire Platinum at $1,180](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/classic-four-prong-solitaire-engagement-ring-item-194156?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) = **from $3,071 total**. For buyers who specifically need natural provenance and GIA certification — the heirloom argument only — this is the rational natural entry build. Above 1ct natural elongated cushion, The Lab Sovereign math makes the natural case increasingly difficult to justify on anything but principle.

## FAQs: Elongated Cushion Cut Lab Grown Diamond

**What is an elongated cushion cut lab grown diamond?**
An elongated cushion cut lab grown diamond is a lab-created diamond (grown via HPHT or CVD process) cut in the cushion shape with a length-to-width ratio of 1.10 or higher. Lab grown origin means it is chemically identical to a natural diamond, with the same optical performance and hardness, at 70–90% lower price. "Elongated" refers to the L/W ratio above 1.10 — filter to 1.15–1.25 when shopping to ensure genuine elongation.

**What is the elongated cushion lab grown diamond price?**
An IGI 1.5ct E-VVS2 elongated cushion lab grown diamond costs [$1,422](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/28961887?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) at Blue Nile in {{year}}. A 2ct IGI D-VVS1 costs [$2,606](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/28884982?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational). A 3ct IGI D-VVS1 costs [$6,215](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/25630512?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational). Lab grown prices are 70–90% lower than natural equivalents at the same carat and quality grades.

**Should I buy IGI or GIA for a lab grown elongated cushion?**
IGI for lab grown, without exception at current pricing. GIA lab grown certification costs 40–140% more than IGI for equivalent stones. A GIA 2ct D-IF lab cushion costs [$6,792](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/26964675?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) versus [$2,606](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/28884982?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) for IGI D-VVS1 at the same carat. Both certify on the same grading scale; the stone quality difference does not justify the GIA price premium for lab grown diamonds.

**What L/W ratio should I choose for an elongated cushion lab grown diamond?**
Target L/W ratio 1.15–1.25. Below 1.15 is The Elongation Divide's no-man's-land — not clearly elongated in person. Above 1.25, the cushion character erodes toward rectangular. The single best ratio is 1.20: unambiguous elongation, retained cushion soft-corner character, optimal face-up size efficiency, and the most flattering finger-lengthening effect on average finger widths.

**What is the elongated cushion lab grown 2 carat price?**
A 2ct IGI D-VVS1 elongated cushion lab grown diamond costs [$2,606](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/28884982?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) at Blue Nile in {{year}}. A 2ct IGI D-IF costs [$4,782](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/27980784?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational). A GIA-certified 2ct D-IF lab cushion costs [$6,792](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/26964675?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational). Natural 2ct elongated cushions at G-VS1 quality start at approximately $8,500.

**What is the elongated cushion lab grown 3 carat price?**
A 3ct GIA D-VVS1 lab cushion costs [$5,962](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/26315453?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) and an IGI D-VVS1 costs [$6,215](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/25630512?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational). Multiple IGI 3ct D-IF lab cushions are available at [$9,327](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/26749422?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational). Natural 3ct elongated cushions at comparable quality start at $32,692 and reach $78,575+ for D clarity — The Lab Sovereign tier.

**What is the best elongated cushion lab grown diamond?**
The best value pick is the [IGI 1.50ct E-VVS2 at $1,422](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/28961887?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational). The best mid-tier is the [IGI 2ct D-VVS1 at $2,606](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/28884982?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational). The best statement piece is the [IGI 3ct D-VVS1 at $6,215](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/25630512?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational). All three are cushion modified brilliant sub-type and should be filtered to L/W 1.15–1.25 in the individual stone listing.

**What is the elongated cushion modified brilliant lab grown diamond?**
The cushion modified brilliant is the sub-type of cushion cut that has an additional row of pavilion facets, producing a distributed "crushed ice" sparkle pattern across the entire face-up area. For elongated cushions specifically, the modified brilliant ensures even light return along both the long and short axes of the elongated outline. Look for "Modified" in the Blue Nile listing name to confirm this sub-type when purchasing.

**Is lab grown elongated cushion the same as natural elongated cushion visually?**
Yes — no visual difference is detectable under normal examination conditions. A gemologist with laboratory spectroscopy equipment can distinguish lab from natural origin. The human eye under normal lighting cannot. The optical performance, fire, brilliance, and sparkle character of an IGI-certified lab elongated cushion and a GIA-certified natural elongated cushion at equivalent grades are identical in everyday wearing conditions.

**What is The Lab Sovereign for elongated cushion diamonds?**
The Lab Sovereign is the market condition at 3ct and above where natural elongated cushion supply at any reasonable quality has effectively dried up and pricing has reached 5–10× the equivalent lab grown stone's cost. At this tier, lab grown is not just the economical choice — it is the only realistic choice for buyers without six-figure budgets. Natural 3ct G-VVS2 cushions start at $32,692; IGI D-VVS1 lab at 3ct starts at $6,215.

**What setting is best for an elongated cushion lab grown diamond?**
A four-prong solitaire with a narrow, tapered band is the best setting choice for elongated cushion lab grown diamonds. It exposes maximum face-up area, aligns the band's visual weight with the elongated stone's axis, and accommodates the L/W ratio without prong misalignment. The [Petite Solitaire 14K White Gold at $1,000](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/petite-solitaire-engagement-ring-item-194386?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) (1,020 reviews) is the most popular and most consistently proportioned setting for elongated cushion lab stones at Blue Nile.

**Does the elongated cushion lab grown diamond hold its value?**
No — lab grown diamonds of all shapes resell at approximately 5–20% of purchase price. This applies to elongated cushion lab grown diamonds regardless of carat, certification, or grade. Buyers who prioritize resale value should purchase natural GIA-certified diamonds instead. For buyers who plan to wear and keep the ring, the resale value difference is irrelevant, and the lab price advantage ($2,606 for 2ct D-VVS1 vs $8,500+ natural equivalent) is the defining consideration.

**What color grade should I choose for an elongated cushion lab grown diamond?**
D-F colorless grades are recommended for elongated cushion lab grown diamonds set in white gold or platinum, because the elongated format's larger face-up table displays color more visibly than compact round stones. At lab grown prices, upgrading to D or E color from G adds a minimal cost premium — the [IGI 1.5ct E-VVS2 at $1,422](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/28961887?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) already delivers E color at the category's entry price.

